ompared to a GG genotype (<em>OR</em> = 3.06, 95% <em>CI</em>: 1.25~7.50).\n</p><!--table ft1--><!--table-wrap mode="anchored" t5--><div class="table-wrap table anchored whole_rhythm" id="Tab2"><h3>Table 2</h3><!--caption a7--><div class="caption"><p id="__p18">Univariate analysis results of <em>OAS1</em> AND <em>MxA</em> gene SNPs in cases and controls</p></div><div data-largeobj="" data-largeobj-link-rid="largeobj_idm139912158177088" class="xtable"><table frame="hsides" rules="groups" class="rendered small default_table"><thead><tr><th rowspan="1" colspan="1"></th><th align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Cases (%)</th><th align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Controls (%)</th><th align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">OR (95% <em>CI</em>)</th><th align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">\n<em>P</em> value</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">\n<em>OAS1 3\'-</em>UTR</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"></td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"></td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"></td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"></td></tr><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">genotype</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"></td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"></td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"></td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">0.026</td></tr><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x02003;&#x02003;&#x02003;AA</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">39 (59.1)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">23 (36.0)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">1.00</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"></td></tr><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x02003;&#x02003;&#x02003;AG</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">22 (33.3)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">31 (48.4)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">0.42 (0.20~0.89)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">0.022</td></tr><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x02003;&#x02003;&#x02003;GG</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">5 (7.6)</td><td align="left" rowspan=